pullRequest.body:
This PR introduces a typeclass `ComplexShape.Associative` which takes as inputs six complex shapes `c‚ÇÅ`, `c‚ÇÇ`, `c‚ÇÉ`, `c‚ÇÅ‚ÇÇ`, `c‚ÇÇ‚ÇÉ` and `c`, and asserts compatibilities of signs for the associativity of the total complex of a triple complex. It shall also be used in the construction of the associator isomorphism for the tensor product of homological complexes.


---

```suggestion
/-- When we have sic complex shapes `c‚ÇÅ`, `c‚ÇÇ`, `c‚ÇÉ`, `c‚ÇÅ‚ÇÇ`, `c‚ÇÇ‚ÇÉ`, `c`, and total functors
`HomologicalComplex‚ÇÇ C c‚ÇÅ c‚ÇÇ ‚•§ HomologicalComplex C c‚ÇÅ‚ÇÇ`,
`HomologicalComplex‚ÇÇ C c‚ÇÅ‚ÇÇ c‚ÇÉ ‚•§ HomologicalComplex C c`,
`HomologicalComplex‚ÇÇ C c‚ÇÇ c‚ÇÉ ‚•§ HomologicalComplex C c‚ÇÇ‚ÇÉ`,
`HomologicalComplex‚ÇÇ C c‚ÇÅ c‚ÇÇ‚ÇÇ‚ÇÉ ‚•§ HomologicalComplex C c`, we get two ways to
compute the total complex of a triple complex in `HomologicalComplex‚ÇÉ C c‚ÇÅ c‚ÇÇ c‚ÇÉ`, then
under this assumption `[Associator c‚ÇÅ c‚ÇÇ c‚ÇÉ c‚ÇÅ‚ÇÇ c‚ÇÇ‚ÇÉ c]`, these two complexes
canonically identify (without introducing signs). -/
```
The name `Associator`¬†sounds like the name of an isomorphism, but this is a `Prop`, so maybe `Associative` is a better name?
Thanks for the suggestion! I have changed it to `Associative`.
